node.text: Fall road trip in the new @acura RDX. #lookup #acurapartner

node.accessibility_caption: Women standing in front of large mountain partially obscured by fog.

node.text:
Foggy mornings in the mountains. Life has felt a lot like this photo lately. Obscured views with fleeting moments of clarity to bring me back to my purpose. Grateful that I have these places to escape to when I loose track of my why.  Over the course of my life, nature has always been my favorite teacher. 

P.S. I haven’t thought about summiting Rainier in a long time… but something about this morning has the idea running through my mind again.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by J E S S on September 09, 2021 tagging @jess.wandering. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Hiking in the US is a completely different vibe from Italy. Walk a few miles in the US and you’ll likely find a little slice of wilderness and a big serving of solitude. Do the same thing in Italy and you’re more likely to stumble on a mountain hut and a big serving of pasta. And I for one, am here for both experiences! ⛰ 🍝 😋
-
Photos: @everchanginghorizon

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by J E S S in Lake Tahoe with @everchanginghorizon, @jess.wandering, and @breezeturner. May be an image of nature and body of water.

node.text:
I just got back into service after a week spent rafting down the Grand Canyon. It was an amazing experience and the longest I've been completely disconnected for a while. 

When I hiked out of the canyon yesterday, the first thing I noticed was that the flag at the visitor center was at half-mast. It was a stark reminder of what a privilege it is to be able to voluntarily disconnect. To let current events, news cycles, and natural disasters fade into oblivion. To reduce the world down to my immediate environment. 

From floods to wildfires and everything in between, my heart aches for everyone out there right now that can't afford to disconnect. Whose very existence feels threatened by ever-changing forces outside their control. Stay safe out there. ♥️
-
Photo: @everchanginghorizon

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by J E S S on August 21, 2021 tagging @jess.wandering. May be an image of 1 person, standing and body of water.

node.text:
There’s a lot of pressure out there to go new places, create unique art, be completely original at all times. You shouldn’t go to “over shot” locations. And if you do, god forbid you “comp stomp.” Do that, and you’re the worst kind of human being. Or at least that seems to be the prevailing attitude. 

And I get it. I really do. There’s a strong argument to be made that all this running around to the same locations, jumping on trends, and recreating images stifles creativity. But here’s the thing, so does putting pressure on yourself to always be radically different and unique. Creativity doesn’t thrive under judgement. It grows out of inspiration. 

I guess what I’m trying to say is… some places are famous for a reason. It’s okay to want to see those destinations. To experience them for yourself. And maybe even take a few pictures while you’re at it. Who knows, the simple act of being in a beautiful place, may be the seed of inspiration you’re looking for. Balance in everything. Have fun out there!
-
Photos: @everchanginghorizon

node.text:
Hold your breath. Make a wish. Count to three. Come with me, and you’ll be in a world of pure imagination. 🐝💜

Location: Dolomites, Italy 
Video: @everchanginghorizon

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by J E S S in Dolomiten - Südtirol with @jess.wandering. May be an image of 1 person, standing and nature.

node.text:
We’ve been taking it a bit slower in Italy this time around. Camping up in mountain huts, waking up with the sun, and eating lots and lots of Tiramisu. In fact, I think we’ve caught every sunset from behind a plate of pasta… and I’m not even mad about it. 🍝😋
-
Photo: @everchanginghorizon

I just finish up a great weekend working with @hyundaiusa to put the new Sport Adventure Vehicle, the Santa Cruz, to the test. We explored all around Santa Cruz from the redwoods to the coast. These were some of my favorite road trips stops along the way: 

Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk 
Watch Surfers At Steamer Lane 
Wilder Ranch State Park 
Shark Fin Cove 
Bigfoot Discovery Museum 
Mountain Biking Hwy 9 Trails
Big Basin 
You Pick Strawberry Farms 

With its unique combo of small SUV size and versatile Open Bed, the Hyundai Santa Cruz made getting around with all our gear a cinch. Now we are off to the next adventure! 

#HyundaySantaCruz #MySantaCruzJourney

node.text:
All year, every year, I look forward to summer at home in Washington. I research new backpacking trips, make hiking bucket lists, daydream about lazy days spent out on the lake with friends. And every year, all of a sudden it’s August, and I’ve hardly spent any time at home at all. Don’t get me wrong, I’m grateful for the opportunities, the obligations, and everything in between. But I do miss these classic PNW scenes. Anyone else feel like their summer is absolutely flying by? I suppose there’s always September. 😉
-
Photo: @everchanginghorizon

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by J E S S on July 31, 2021 tagging @jess.wandering. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
My bucket list guide to Zakynthos, Greece is finally up on the blog! It has all my favorite photography spots, best things to do, and tons of yummy restaurants, and beautiful accommodations. I can honestly say it’s one of the more stunning places I’ve been, and I hope that if you ever have the chance to go this guide will help you plan the perfect trip. 🌞 💙 (save this post to keep it on your bucket list!) 

Also, thanks so much to everyone that sent me recommendations for places to stay and eat. I made sure to include the most popular ones in the post, since that’s not really my area of expertise. 🤓

Photos: @everchanginghorizon shot on Sony a7rIII #bealpha @sonyalpha
